 Google Colab Runtime Configuration:
GPU:

NVIDIA Tesla T4, P100, or V100 (available via Runtime > Change runtime type > GPU)

16GB GPU memory (approx. for T4/P100)

CPU:

2-core to 4-core Xeon CPUs (shared environment)

RAM:

~12GB (standard) to ~26GB (Colab Pro)

Disk Space:

~50GB of temporary storage

Recommended Runtime Settings:
Use GPU as the hardware accelerator.

Recommended for training with moderate-sized datasets (e.g., <10,000 images at 512x512 resolution).

For large datasets or prolonged training, use Google Colab Pro or Colab Pro+ for extended session times and higher memory limits.

